Package stincmale.ratmex.meter

Class RateMeterConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • stincmale.ratmex.meter.RateMeterConfig
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConcurrentRateMeterConfig

    @Immutable
public class RateMeterConfig
extends java.lang.Object
    A configuration that can be used to create AbstractRateMeter.

    The default values:

    • getTicksCounterSupplier() - LongTicksCounter::new
    • getTimeSensitivity() - Optional.empty()
    • getHistoryLength() - 2

      • getTicksCounterSupplier

        public final java.util.function.Function<java.lang.Long,? extends TicksCounter> getTicksCounterSupplier​()
        Specifies a supplier which must be used by AbstractRateMeter to create ticks counters. Note that if AbstractRateMeter is used concurrently, then the supplier must provide a thread-safe TicksCounter. If this constraint is violated, then the behavior is unspecified.

      • getTimeSensitivity

        public final java.util.Optional<java.time.Duration> getTimeSensitivity​()
        An empty time sensitivity means that AbstractRateMeter will automatically use samples interval / 20 as the time sensitivity, which in turn means that the samples interval must be a multiple of 20.
        See Also:
        RateMeter.getTimeSensitivity()

      • getHistoryLength

        public final int getHistoryLength​()
        Specifies the length of samples history measured in samplesInterval units. A RateMeter may choose to maintain samples history longer than specified by this property.

        Note that the specification of RateMeter states that any RateMeter must maintain samples history for at least 2samplesInterval.

        The longer history a RateMeter maintains, the less likely a measurement can be inaccurate.
